	<text id="ruskin_to_joan_july_22_1867">
	    
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>2003L01527</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>           
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-07-22"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">22nd July 1867.</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest wee <rs key="76205504" type="person">Doanie</rs></salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	            
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I hope you will be very happy - to-day - to-morrow and ever after - and that you will always be happier because of your good brother to-day made yours and not less happy in your tiresome querulous cuzzie - you know - it <hi rend="underline">must</hi> be nice having somebody to scold sometimes - and one <hi rend="underline">must'nt</hi> one's husband!</s>
	                <s id="s2">- Mind that (and tell<rs key="k_simson" type="person">Kate</rs>)  and love me always and believe me ever your loving Cousin.</s>
	            </p>
	            
	            <closer>
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">John Ruskin</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
	            <postscript>
	                <p id="p2">
	                    <s id="s3">You were to have had a long letter but I've been out in the rain, &amp; hindered.</s>
	                    <s id="s4">but I'm getting stronger I've been climbing to-day as high as your highest hill <add hand="#JR" place="below">(1400)</add>, in the rain &amp; wind.</s>           
	                </p>   
	            </postscript>
	        </div>
	    </body>
